<p>I have some input variables with a dynamic name into my form (UUID). To avoid error I test if the variables are defined, but strangely the function IsDefined return me an error (when the field is not sent like a radio or check-box).</p>  <p>The HTML result in the form:</p>  <pre><code> Yes &lt;input type="radio"id="content_BB66F151-CB09-1C8C-CCF53DE1A92652FC" name="content_BB66F151-CB09-1C8C-CCF53DE1A92652FC" value="1"&gt;   No &lt;input type="radio" id="content_BB66F151-CB09-1C8C-CCF53DE1A92652FC" name="content_BB66F151-CB09-1C8C-CCF53DE1A92652FC" value="0"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>My CFM: </p>  <pre><code>Yes &lt;input type="radio" id="content_#qMD.MD_FIELD_ID#"                         name="content_#qMD.MD_FIELD_ID#" value="1"&gt; No &lt;input type="radio" id="content_#qMD.MD_FIELD_ID#" name="content_#qMD.MD_FIELD_ID#" value="0"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>My CFM test: I have a list of all MD_FIELD_ID and loop over them</p>  <pre><code>&lt;cfloop list="#attributes.lMetadataField#" index="MD_FIELD_ID" delimiters="," &gt; &lt;cfif IsDefined("attributes.content_" &amp; MD_FIELD_ID)&gt; &lt;/cfif&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Coldfusion return me this when the field is not in the submitted form:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Parameter 1 of function IsDefined, which is now attributes.content_BB66F151-CB09-1C8C-CCF53DE1A92652FC, must be a syntactically valid variable name.</p> </blockquote>  <p>I have tried different syntaxes: </p>  <pre><code> IsDefined("attributes.content_#MD_FIELD_ID#") or attributes["content_#MD_FIELD_ID#"] </code></pre>  <p>but always the same error. If the field is in the submitted form, it works fine.</p>  <p>What is wrong in my code ?</p>